Key Match Events: Habib Diallo netted in the 27th minute with a headed goal from a long cross by Pape Matar Sarr to put Senegal at the top of Group B with victory in Nouakchott
Miscellaneous Highlights: There was a lengthy delay in completing the match after frustrated home fans threw objects towards the pitch in the second half and proceedings were halted
Others: Senegal are one point above Sudan and the Democratic Republic of Congo in the group standings
Tunisia have a two-point lead in Group H over Namibia with Liberia a further point back in third place
